title: SEC charges Do Kwon, Terraform with fraud in connection with Terra collapse
description: The SEC charged Terraform and its CEO, Do Kwon, with fraud, alleging that they bilked investors out of billions of dollars.

title: Biden says three recently downed aerial objects were not linked to Chinese spy program
description: The remarks came after days of mounting pressure from Congress, which wants to hear exactly what the administration knew about the spy balloon.

title: Microsoft's Bing A.I. is producing creepy conversations with users
description: Artificial intelligence experts warned that large language models have issues including "hallucination," which means that the software can make stuff up.

title: YouTube CEO Susan Wojcicki says she's stepping down
description: YouTube CEO Susan Wojcicki said on Thursday that she's stepping down.

title: Renault CEO questions wisdom of electric vehicle price cuts
description: "The last thing I'm going to do is to compromise on the margins ... of electric cars," Renault CEO Luca de Meo told CNBC.

title: Chinese smartphone giant Oppo launches foldable flip phone as it bets on high-end market
description: The Find N2 Flip marks Oppo's push to make a dent in the premium segment of the smartphone market, in a challenge to Samsung.

title: Sanctions on Russian oil are having the 'intended effect,' IEA says
description: Bans and price caps targeting Russian oil are having the "intended effect" despite surprisingly resilient exports in recent months, according to the International Energy Agency.

title: Europe considers a digital currency as it strives to counter U.S. and China's tech dominance
description: The European Central Bank is worried that the euro zone will end up in a "sandwich position" between U.S. Big Tech and China's payment systems.

title: Bitcoin surges 11% despite U.S. crackdown, as crypto market gains $84 billion in value
description: Bitcoin rose to its highest level since August, as the market shrugged off a tougher regulatory stance from U.S. regulators.

title: Standard Chartered 'absolutely not' for sale, bank CEO says
description: The CEO of Standard Chartered said the bank was 'absolutely not' for sale on CNBC's "Squawk Box Europe."

title: A 'cocktail' of sticky inflation and a tight labor market boosts Bank of England rate hike bets
description: A tight labor market and comparatively slow return to earth for inflation means the Bank of England is likely to press ahead with a further interest rate hike in March, economists suggest.

title: CNBC Daily Open: U.S. stocks don't seem bothered by inflation, ignore jump in retail sales
description: January's retail sales, like the months' jobs report and consumer price index, were higher than expected. But stocks don't seem concerned anymore.

title: Rise of 'zombie' VCs haunts tech investors as plunging valuations hammer the industry
description: For some venture capitalists, we're approaching a night of the living dead.

title: MSCI delays weighting cuts for two Adani companies, cites 'replicability' concerns
description: Index provider MSCI said it will delay implementing weighting changes for some Adani Group companies until later this year.

title: Adani's fall reignites scrutiny of billionaire's close ties with Modi
description: The tycoon found the ground sinking beneath his feet and the fortunes of his businesses plummeting after a short-sellers report.

title: Ford F-150 Lightning production halt was triggered by vehicle battery fire
description: The update comes a day after Ford confirmed production of the F-150 Lightning had been suspended over a potential battery issue.

title: Google asks employees to rewrite Bard's bad responses, says the A.I. 'learns best by example'
description: As Google races to get its artificial intelligence search tool up to speed, it wants employees to flag incorrect answers and even rewrite them.
